{"word":"ἄτομος","slug":"ἄτομος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄτομος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>τέμνω</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>uncut, unmown</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>that cannot be cut, indivisible</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; <el>ἐν ἀτόμωι</el> in a <i>moment</i>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}